      • addEmployee

        public void addEmployee(Map<String,Object> params,
               ISirqulCallback<WrappedResponse<AccountResponse>> callback)
        Create a new account record with the provided information.

        Target API Endpoint: /employee/create

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the logged in user
        • SirqulKeys.managerAccountId
          The account id of the manager to assign under
        • SirqulKeys.prefixName
          The name prefix; Mr, Mrs, etc
        • SirqulKeys.firstName
          The first name
        • SirqulKeys.middleName
          The middle name
        • SirqulKeys.lastName
          The last name
        • SirqulKeys.suffixName
          The name suffix; Jr, Sr, III, etc
        • SirqulKeys.title
          The title of the user
        • SirqulKeys.username
          The username/email for the new user. This must be unique across the entire the system.
        • SirqulKeys.password
          The password for the new user
        • SirqulKeys.gender
          The gender {MALE, FEMALE, ANY}
        • SirqulKeys.homePhone
          The home phone number
        • SirqulKeys.cellPhone
          The cellular phone number
        • SirqulKeys.cellPhoneCarrier
          The cellular service provider. This is required for sending SMS. Leave this empty if the provider is not on the list of supported carriers. Supported Carriers: {ATT, QWEST, T_MOBILE, VERIZON, SPRINT, VIRIGIN_MOBILE, NEXTEL, ALLTEL, METRO_PCS, POWERTEL, BOOST_MOBILE, SUNCOM, TRACFONE, US_CELLULAR}
        • SirqulKeys.businessPhone
          The business phone number
        • SirqulKeys.emailAddress
          The user's contact email address (NOT the username)
        • SirqulKeys.streetAddress
          The street address of the user's contact location
        • SirqulKeys.streetAddress2
          Additional address information (such as a suite number, floor number, building name, or PO Box)
        • SirqulKeys.city
          The city of the user's contact location
        • SirqulKeys.state
          The state of the user's contact location
        • The zipcode of the user's contact location
        • SirqulKeys.country
          The country of the user's contact location
        • SirqulKeys.role
          The role, type Enums.AccountType; RETAILER or RETAILER_LIMITED, defaulted to RETAILER_LIMITED

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a WrappedResponse<AccountResponse> on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        EmployeeApiBase.addEmployee

        public void searchEmployees(Map<String,Object> params,
                   ISirqulCallback<AccountListResponse> callback)
        Use the accountId to determine the associated BillableEntity. From there get a list of all accounts associated as managers/employees.

        Target API Endpoint: /employee/search

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account id of the logged in user
        • SirqulKeys.role
          The role to limit the search to: RETAILER or RETAILER_LIMITED. Leave empty to search on both roles.
        • SirqulKeys.retailerId
          the retailer id
        • SirqulKeys.retailerLocationId
          the retailer location id
        • SirqulKeys.keyword
          Match a keyword to the first name, last name, or username
        • SirqulKeys.sortField
          the sort field
        • SirqulKeys.descending
          the descending
        • SirqulKeys.start
          Start the result set at some index
        • SirqulKeys.limit
          Limit the result to some number
        • SirqulKeys.activeOnly
          the active only

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a AccountListResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred.
